<br>
I used the Epic pet, though 57 earth with DS could probably do just as well except that they run at low HP, and the earth pet would root them, thus taking extra damage.  They also proc a lure disease based DoT, so the damage taken by rooting the mob when it would normally run might be offset by resisting their DoT.<br>
<br>
I also had a friend give me Koadics whenever he was on, and travelled to purchase it from other 60 chanters when he wasn't.<br>
<br>
You can park your pet outside the Sun Revenant Castle on the edge of the plateau, use the Clay Braclet (instant click, unlimited charges, eye of zomm) to scout inside and target the next mob, click off Eye of Zomm and then use Malosini or any free damage nuke to pull (I used Boots of Bladecalling, then Malosini as they were incoming).  Keep in mind that you can cast through the wall of the castle as it's an outdoor zone.  Bolts will still be blocked by the wall however.<br>
<br>
Two sorts of mobs: a Sun Revenant, warrior, and a Sun Reaver, necro (though never summons a pet).<br>
<br>
They're mainly blue in 59, with a rare light blue.<br>
At 60, 1/3 or more are light blue spawns.<br>
<br>
Healing the pet, or reclaim &amp; chain casting pets is probably more efficient than nuking.<br>
<br>
There's about 14 mobs all up, on a 26 or 27 minute spawn.  The camp is often quite contested. <p><FONT FACE="Comic Sans MS,Arial" SIZE="3"><A HREF="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=59365" TARGET="_blank">Kathodos</A> <A HREF="http://www.wreckerguild.org/" TARGET="_blank">&lt;Wreckers&gt;</A></FONT> - Battle Cleric of Tunare - Tholuxe Paells<BR>
